content.description: Pretend that you in the gym and the floor is right under you.     Big moves on Big holds to a high top out.  Perfect to get blood flowing and to get use to topping out 20 ft off the deck.
content.location: Left face of the "Office Project" boulder.

content.description: This is the scary left trending exit on the "Office Project" Boulder.     Sit start on good side pull make one move over the pedestal landing then trend left through an under-cling into definite no fall territory.   You will have good side pulls and one really high step to a committing move to a good sloper. Then jugs at the lip.    Keep breathing and stay calm this climb is not for the faint of heart.
content.protection: As many pads as you can find and some dedicated friends to spot. (I suggest dialing the moves in with a rope first then going for the send)
content.location: On the Lake side of the boulder.

content.description: This boulder sticks out like a sore thumb in the talus field to the north of the lost and found area, it's simply huge!  On the downhill face of this boulder is a difficult thin climb.  All the holds are there, it was just over my head.  Landing is a flat elevated pedestal.  A little heady to spot, but should be fairly safe. A proud line there for the taking.
content.location: Top of the talus to the north of the "Lost and Found" and "Whaler's" areas. Approximately 200 feet north of "Hybrid Wanderer".

content.description: Good Route.  Start 4 feet left of small tree on crimps and delicately climb the thin face.  Find a good flat hold at the bottom of a triangular niche to gun for at the top.
content.location: Follow the contour to the north a couple hundred feet past the Wizard to another cliff band. There are a few other easier looking routes along this cliff band. Â This is just before you come to Levitation.

content.description: A very large and very squared off boulder.
